  "description": "Saltwax Stockroom occupies a low, interior chamber tucked beneath the lodging’s steep central stair, its brick walls limewashed and scored with tally marks. Iron-banded shelving and pegged racks hold sealed crockery, saltwax blocks, lamp oil tins, and bundled linens, all arranged for quick accounting under contract. A narrow shuttered slit window admits guarded light, while interdiction placards and hazard codes are nailed above the lock-hasped door in the same plain script used throughout the house.",
